A.10. class TEnv: see above
  notes: - It is allowable for handlers to deregister while threaded.
  warning: - See THStack::warning
	   - This class can change the auto-repeat setting of the display.
	     If it is not properly destructed (ie the program terminates
	     ungracefully), this setting is not reset. Whether pointer-grab
	     is reset under such conditions depends on the X implementation.

A.11. Keyboard handling
During a key() event (only), you may use lastchar() to obtain an ASCII repr.
Apart from codes 32-126, the following are returned:
       8      Backspace
       9      Tab
      13      Return/Enter
      27      Escape/Pause/Break
     127      Delete
256+8/9/10/11 Left/Right/Down/Up
512+8/9/10/11 Home/End/PgDn/PgUp

B. TCmap

B.1 class TRGB: RGB 8+8+8 bit colour rep
  constr.: TRGB(r,g,b), TRGB(grey), TRGB(), TRGB(char*/string)
  methods: =(TRGB), +=(TRGB), -=(TRGB), +=(int), -=(int)
  notes: - RGB values are automatically clipped to 0..255 after every op.
         - TRGB(string) takes "int int int" or "float,float,float",
	   with int in 0..255 resp. float in [0,1).
  warning: TRGB(string) does NOT take an X colour name.

