F. TImage
  constr.: TImage(TEnv,w,h)
  methods: int width(), height(), depth(); TEnv tenv();
	   void putpix(x,y,TCol);
	   TCol getpix(x,y);
  notes: - In the UNIX vsn, TImage is based on XImage.
	 - putpix() and getpix() are supposed to be quick. In the UNIX vsn,
	   they are inline and use the XImage's put_pixel() and get_pixel()
	   routines directly.
  warning: - Device dependent header file...	
	   - TSprites can be written to the main window *much* quicker in the
	     UNIX vsn.

G. TImageFile
  constr.: TImageFile(TEnv, basename, read, write)
  methods: TImage *readimage(name/num, dest=0)
	   int addimage(TImage*, name)
	   static bool exist(TEnv, basename)
  notes: - The actual filename is the basename plus the cmap's id().
